HEADWORD: Audition
<hw>Au*di"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>auditio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of hearing or listening;
hearing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Audition</qex> may be active or passive; hence the difference
between listening and simple hearing.</q>
<rj><qau>Dunglison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Auditive</ent>⟦br⟧
